# binance example: runtime log output (redb databases / FileLog dirs), any private key placed
# alongside the example rather than referenced via BINANCE_FIX_PRIVATE_KEY, and env.example itself
# -- despite the name, this one carries real (if testnet-scoped) credentials copied from a
# developer's local setup, not placeholder values, so it MUST NOT be committed.
/log/
crates/truefix/examples/binance/log/
crates/truefix/examples/binance/*.pem
crates/truefix/examples/binance/env.example
